-- Three U.K. Men Plead Guilty to Prepping for Terror Attack
-- B y   J e r e m y   H o d g e s
-- 2013-03-15T12:29:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-15/three-u-k-men-plead-guilty-to-prepping-for-terror-attack.html
Three British men pleaded guilty to
charges of preparing to commit terrorist acts at a London court
today.  Richard Dart, 29, Imran Mahmood, 21, and Jahangir Alom, 26,
appeared via video link at London’s Central  Criminal Court  and
admitted to the charges. Sentencing is expected to come at the
end of April, according to the court clerk.  The three men were charged with “the intention of
committing acts of terrorism or assisting another to commit such
acts,” including traveling to  Pakistan  for training, according
to the indictment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeremy Hodges in London at 
 jhodges17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at 
 aaarons@bloomberg.net  